main event: Three unidentified objects were reported over Jacksonville, Pennsylvania on June 21, 1952.
interesting points: The report indicates that photographs were taken of the objects, but they are not included in the document.
The duration of the observation is not reported.
The conclusion of the report states there was 'INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR EVALUATION'.
The report includes a questionnaire-style form with detailed questions about the sighting, such as weather conditions, brightness of the objects, and their movements.
The report also includes a blank sketch where the witness was instructed to draw the motion and arrangement of the objects.
photographs: yes, but not included in the report
